From 698af0d517312372f0babddf4cba00d8f4448aed Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Thu, 21 May 2026 17:54:36 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Migrate entire stack from Firebase to Supabase + Cloudflare
 R2

Replace Firebase Firestore, Firebase Auth (secondary), and Firebase Storage
with Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth + Realtime) and Cloudflare R2 (object storage
via presigned URLs) across all pages, components, and lib files.

Key changes:
- All Firestore onSnapshot listeners replaced with Supabase postgres_changes realtime channels + initial fetch
- All Firestore CRUD (addDoc, updateDoc, deleteDoc, setDoc) replaced with supabase.from(...).insert/update/delete
- arrayUnion/arrayRemove replaced with spread/filter on in-memory state
- writeBatch replaced with Promise.all of parallel supabase updates
- runTransaction replaced with sequential supabase reads + writes
- serverTimestamp() replaced with new Date().toISOString()
- Firebase Storage replaced with R2 via presigned upload/download URL API routes
- Secondary Firebase Auth for admin user creation replaced with /api/admin/create-user route using supabaseAdmin
- All snake_case DB columns mapped to camelCase TypeScript types via fromRow() helpers
- Added supabase/schema.sql with full PostgreSQL schema, RLS policies, and realtime config
- TypeScript errors resolved across all migrated files

